FBIS3-23123 "jptot010__l94086" JPRS-TOT-94-010-L Document Type:JPRS Document Title:Terrorism FOUO 10 March 1994 NEAR EAST/SOUTH ASIA ISRAEL Update on, Reactions to Hebron Mosque Massacre Hebron Jews Detained, Kakh Leaders Escape TA2702055294 Jerusalem Qol Yisra'el in English 0500 GMT 27 Feb 94 TA2702055294 Jerusalem Qol Yisra'el Language: English Article Type:BFN [Excerpt] [passage omitted] Mark Weiss reports: In what appears to be the first stage of the expected crack down on the extremist fringe within the settler community, security forces detained overnight a number of Jewish residents of Hebron. Residents of Qiryat Arba' also reported that soldiers came to detain Kakh leaders Barukh Marzel and No'am Federman, but the two managed to escape. [passage omitted]
